attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: Capsaicin IoT botnet variant (derived from Kaiten/Ziggy/Qbot codebases). The binary functions as an IRC-controlled backdoor with extensive DDoS capabilities including DNS amplification, HTTP flooding, and ICMP 'Blacknurse' attacks. It exhibits typical botnet behaviors such as process killing of competitors ('botkill'), self-persistence via '/etc/rc.d/rc.local', telnet brute-force scanning ('ak47scan'), and iptables-based fast-flux proxying. IOCs include the C2 command set (STD, HOLD, JUNK, LOCKUP), the string 'Kaiten ZiggyStartux Capsaicin Fast-Flux Qbot Redo by Freak', and the download URL 'http://pirati[.]abuser[.]eu/yak.sh'.
